---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Remnant Inventory Monetization for Publishers | AdBunny"
  description="Fill unsold ad slots with AdBunny. One JS tag, AI-optimized banner selection, zero conflict with your existing ad stack. Start monetizing today."
  keywords="remnant inventory monetization for publishers, unsold ad space, fill rate optimization, backfill ad monetization"
>

<section class="pt-28 pb-12 max-md:pt-20">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <div class="max-w-[44rem]">
      <h1 class="font-extrabold leading-[1.05] tracking-tight mb-4" style="font-size:clamp(2.25rem,5vw,3.5rem)">Monetize every impression your current stack doesn't fill</h1>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-[34rem]" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">If you're running direct deals or header bidding, you already know some percentage of your inventory goes unsold or fills at a discount. AdBunny catches that gap.</p>
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Your JS Tag</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dark-noise py-20 max-md:py-14" style="background:var(--color-surface)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8" style="position:relative;z-index:2">
    <div class="max-w-[40rem]">
      <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-4">The remnant inventory problem</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Even well-optimized ad stacks leave impressions on the table — geos with thin demand, times of day with low bid density, slots outside your top placements. Traditionally, publishers deal with this using a fixed waterfall: call network A, then B, then C, in a set order, regardless of what's actually the best-paying option for that specific impression. It's simple, but it leaves revenue behind.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-20 max-md:py-14">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-10">How AdBunny fills the gap</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-10 max-md:grid-cols-1">
      <div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">01</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Sits below your primary stack</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">AdBunny is a backfill layer, not a replacement. It only evaluates inventory your existing direct deals and header bidding partners didn't fill.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">02</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">AI picks the best banner per impression</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Instead of a static call order, AdBunny's optimization layer evaluates real-time demand for each individual impression and serves whichever banner is likely to pay the most.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">03</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">One tag, no dev lift</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No line items to configure, no waterfall to maintain, no new SDK for your engineering team to integrate. Paste the tag, done.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dark-noise py-20 max-md:py-14" style="background:var(--color-surface)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8" style="position:relative;z-index:2">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-10">What you get</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-10 max-md:grid-cols-1">
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Higher fill rate on remnant slots</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">AI-driven yield optimization instead of a static, out-of-date waterfall.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Zero interference with primary demand</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No conflict with your existing direct-sold or header-bidding demand.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Same-day setup</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">One tag, no ad-ops overhead, no engineering sprint required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-20 max-md:py-14">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <div class="max-w-[40rem]">
      <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-4">Who this is for</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Publishers and app developers of any size dealing with unsold or underperforming banner inventory — from independent sites supplementing a small ad stack to larger publishers looking to squeeze more yield out of remnant slots without adding ad-ops overhead.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-20 max-md:py-14 text-center">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.5rem)] font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Your remnant inventory is worth more than it's earning</h2>
    <p class="text-base mb-8" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">See what AI-optimized backfill can do for your fill rate.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Get Your JS Tag</a>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
